		<h1 class="entry-title">Abstract class in Java</h1>

<p>A class that is declared with abstract keyword, is known as abstract class in java. It can have abstract and concrete methods (method with body).
</p> It needs to be extended and its method implemented.<p> It cannot be instantiated.</p>
<p><b>Abstraction in Java</b></p>

Abstraction is a process of hiding the implementation details and showing only functionality to the user.

<p>Abstraction shows only important things to the user and hides the internal details.</p>
<p> Example: sending Email, you just type the text and send the Email. You don't know the internal processing about the Email delivery.</p>
<p><b>There are two ways to achieve abstraction in java</b>

<p>1.Abstract class </p>
<p>2.Interface </p>
